{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_019cVFiUQQuEzG6AgRPNVsTi","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Oracle passes. Here's what was done:\n\n**Root cause:** The Elasticsearch cluster had no file realm configured — the `es-file-realm-aggregate` secret (ops-user only) and `user-provided-file-realm` secret (report-user) existed but were neither merged nor mounted into the pods.\n\n**Changes made:**\n\n1. **Merged secrets** — Updated `es-file-realm-aggregate` to include both `ops-user` and `report-user` entries (users + users_roles from the `user-provided-file-realm` secret).\n\n2. **Enabled file realm** — Added `xpack.security.authc.realms.file.file1.order: 0` to the `es-config` ConfigMap's `elasticsearch.yml`.\n\n3. **Mounted realm files** — Patched the `es-cluster` StatefulSet to add the `es-file-realm-aggregate` secret as a volume, with `subPath` mounts placing `users` and `users_roles` at `/usr/share/elasticsearch/config/`.\n\n4. **Rolling restart** — The StatefulSet performed an automatic rolling restart (all 3 pods updated, cluster stayed healthy/green throughout).\n\n5. **Seeded index** — Created the `app-data` index and a seed document (the precondition seeding had failed because the file realm wasn't configured at the time it ran).\n\n`report-user` can now read `app-data` (viewer role grants index read), `ops-user` retains superuser access, and the `elastic` built-in user is unaffected."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":177,"cache_read_input_tokens":55163,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":177},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"f341285b-a58b-4c9a-b817-6d1b0282d533","uuid":"e27fb625-f7cc-457c-b8b8-1ff82e7e704a","request_id":"req_011CccHid7zLcsCjRU4